Key Objectives of a SOC

üîç Continuous Monitoring ‚Äì Track logs, alerts, and events in real time

üö® Threat Detection ‚Äì Identify malware, phishing, intrusions, and anomalies

üõ†Ô∏è Incident Response ‚Äì Contain, eradicate, and recover from attacks

üìä Compliance & Reporting ‚Äì Support audits and security standards

üîÅ Continuous Improvement ‚Äì Tune rules, reduce false positives



---

SOC Team Roles (Hierarchy)

Role	Responsibility

SOC L1 Analyst	Monitor alerts, initial triage, escalate
SOC L2 Analyst	Deep investigation, correlation, containment
SOC L3 Analyst	Advanced threats, malware analysis, IR
SOC Manager	Operations, KPIs, compliance
Threat Hunter	Proactive threat discovery
IR / DFIR	Incident response & forensics



---

Tools Used in SOC

SIEM: Splunk, QRadar, ArcSight, Sentinel

EDR/XDR: CrowdStrike, Defender, SentinelOne

SOAR: Palo Alto XSOAR, Splunk SOAR

Network Security: Firewalls, IDS/IPS

Threat Intel: VirusTotal, AbuseIPDB, MISP

Ticketing: ServiceNow, JIRA



---

Daily Activities in SOC

Alert monitoring & triage

Log analysis (Windows, Linux, Firewall, AD)

Incident investigation

Phishing email analysis

Escalation & documentation

Shift handover reports



---

Skills Required for SOC

Technical

Networking (TCP/IP, DNS, HTTP, Ports)

Windows & Linux basics (logs, processes)

Cybersecurity fundamentals

Log analysis & SIEM queries

MITRE ATT&CK framework


Soft Skills

Attention to detail

Documentation & communication

Working in shifts (24√ó7)



